01:17:57.000 --> 01:18:01.000
So apathy is like a really important word.

01:18:01.000 --> 01:18:03.000
The Greek word is apathy.

01:18:03.000 --> 01:18:05.000
It means without passions.

01:18:05.000 --> 01:18:14.000
And the Stoics, who you mentioned earlier, really thought that passions are what get in the way if you're living well.

01:18:14.000 --> 01:18:18.000
Because to live well, you have to think clearly about what you should do.

01:18:18.000 --> 01:18:25.000
And you shouldn't let your resentments and your angers and your petty animosities direct your behavior.

01:18:25.000 --> 01:18:28.000
You should release yourself from those kinds of passions.

01:18:28.000 --> 01:18:32.000
So Stoicism, again, huge caricature.

01:18:32.000 --> 01:18:37.000
But it's an aim not to care because caring is bad.

01:18:37.000 --> 01:18:49.000
And there's certain forms of existentialism, certainly in Pascal and Kierkegaard and Dostoyevsky and Heidegger and Sart in his own way.

01:18:49.000 --> 01:18:57.000
So it's not just a theistic or atheistic thing, where what's crucial about us is that we do care.

01:18:57.000 --> 01:19:00.000
Heidegger says care is the being of Dasein.

01:19:00.000 --> 01:19:02.000
Dasein is his name for us.

01:19:02.000 --> 01:19:06.000
What it is to be us is to be the being that already cares.

01:19:06.000 --> 01:19:09.000
And you can't not do that.

01:19:09.000 --> 01:19:13.000
You can pretend you're not doing it, but you're just caring in a different way.

01:19:13.000 --> 01:19:17.000
It's like Sart saying you can pretend you're not taking responsibility.

01:19:17.000 --> 01:19:21.000
Or you could pretend that you don't have to make a decision.

01:19:21.000 --> 01:19:23.000
That is making a decision.

01:19:23.000 --> 01:19:25.000
Not caring is a way of caring.

01:19:25.000 --> 01:19:31.000
And so I think the existentialists that I'm interested in think that we do care.

01:19:31.000 --> 01:19:34.000
That's constitutive of what it is to be us.

01:19:34.000 --> 01:19:37.000
And so they all think that the Stoics got it wrong.

01:19:37.000 --> 01:19:49.000
But that leaves open a huge range of moves about how we inhabit that existence well.

