01:32:44.000 --> 01:32:50.000
You ask from an existential perspective and there's lots of different positions that you could have.

01:32:50.000 --> 01:32:57.000
So, let me tell you something in the area of what I think I might believe, which comes out of this tradition.

01:32:57.000 --> 01:32:59.000
And it's this.

01:32:59.000 --> 01:33:13.000
If you live in a community where people are being dragged down by the norms of the community rather than elevated, then there's two things that you have to recognize.

01:33:13.000 --> 01:33:19.000
One is that you bear some responsibility for that, not necessarily because you chose it.

01:33:19.000 --> 01:33:21.000
Maybe you reviled it.

01:33:21.000 --> 01:33:23.000
Maybe you were against it.

01:33:23.000 --> 01:33:29.000
But there's some way in which we all act in accordance with the norms of our culture.

01:33:29.000 --> 01:33:32.000
We all give in to them in some way or another.

01:33:32.000 --> 01:33:40.000
And if those norms are broken, then there's some way in which we've allowed ourselves to be responsible for broken norms.

01:33:40.000 --> 01:33:43.000
We've become responsible for broken norms.

01:33:43.000 --> 01:33:45.000
And I do think you have to face up to that.

01:33:45.000 --> 01:33:48.000
I think that let's just take gender norms.

01:33:48.000 --> 01:33:50.000
Maybe the gender norms are broken.

01:33:50.000 --> 01:33:56.000
Maybe the way men and women treat one another or the way men treat women is broken.

01:33:56.000 --> 01:33:58.000
Maybe it is.

01:33:58.000 --> 01:34:01.000
I'm not making a substantive claim.

01:34:01.000 --> 01:34:03.000
I'm just saying, lots of people say it is.

01:34:03.000 --> 01:34:18.000
And if you're in a culture where those norms take root, you don't get to just isolate yourself and pull yourself out of the culture and think, I don't have any responsibility.

01:34:18.000 --> 01:34:21.000
You're already a part of the culture.

01:34:21.000 --> 01:34:29.000
Even if you're isolating yourself from it, that's a way of rejecting the sort of part you play in the culture.

01:34:29.000 --> 01:34:32.000
But it's not a way of getting behind it.

01:34:32.000 --> 01:34:35.000
Now you're playing that role differently.

01:34:35.000 --> 01:34:40.000
You're saying, I don't want to take responsibility for what's going on around me.

01:34:40.000 --> 01:34:45.000
And that's a way of taking responsibility by refusing to do it.

01:34:45.000 --> 01:34:50.000
So I think we're implicated in whatever's going on around us.

01:34:50.000 --> 01:34:56.000
And if we're going to do anything in our lives, we ought to recognize that.

01:34:56.000 --> 01:35:12.000
Recognize that even in situations where you maybe didn't decide to do it, you could be part of bringing other people down and then devote yourself to trying to figure out how to act differently so that the norms update themselves.

