02:49:46.000 --> 02:49:57.000
The traditional thing to say in the philosophical tradition, even in the AI tradition, which is a kind of manifestation of philosophy from Plato 4.

02:49:57.000 --> 02:50:06.000
The traditional thing to say is that what characterizes us is our rationality, that we're intelligent beings, that we're the ones that think.

02:50:06.000 --> 02:50:11.000
And I think that's certainly part of what characterizes us.

02:50:11.000 --> 02:50:15.000
But I think there's more to it, too.

02:50:15.000 --> 02:50:34.000
I think we're capable of experiencing simultaneously the complete and utter ungroundedness of everything that's meaningful in our existence and also the real significance of it.

02:50:34.000 --> 02:50:42.000
And that sounds like a contradiction. How could it really be significant and not be based on anything?

02:50:42.000 --> 02:50:46.000
But I think that's the contradiction that somehow characterizes us.

02:50:46.000 --> 02:50:55.000
And I think that we're the being that sort of has to hold that weird mystery before us and live in the light of it.

02:50:55.000 --> 02:50:59.000
That's the thing that I think is really at our core.

02:50:59.000 --> 02:51:03.000
